text.section:
The provisions of this section do not apply to:
Any commodity sold for immediate consumption on the premises where sold;
Vegetables when sold by the head or bunch;
Any commodity in a container standardized by a law of the State or by federal law;
Any commodity in package form when there exists a general consumer usage to express the quantity in some other manner;
Any concrete aggregate, concrete mixture, and loose solid material, such as earth, soil, gravel, crushed stone, and similar materials, when sold by cubic measure; or
Unprocessed vegetable and animal fertilizer when sold by cubic measure.
